thread.title: Senate Readies Votes on Immigration Measures

author: Kristina Peterson
title: Senate Readies Votes on Immigration Measures
text:
WASHINGTON—The Senate prepared to vote Thursday on a series of immigration measures after months of feuding, including a bipartisan compromise aimed at appeasing both parties’ concerns as well as a rival plan drawn up by the White House.
Lawmakers are nearing the end of the one week allotted to immigration debate without knowing if any bill could pass in the chamber, or meet the demands of President Donald Trump.
